title: 1972 - Yes - Close To the Edge [US Atlantic SD 19133-2 WAV][Barr
description: I converted the same file I posted here from FLAC back to WAV and the dynamic range went from 11 to 12.  Proof uncompressed audio sounds better.  It's not the case all the time though.  Too me, it seems like some slower tempo music benefits from it.  I used Foobar2000 to convert it.  I always believed it, and heard differences.  Just like Pink Floyd Dark Side Of The Moon SACD Uncompressed.  It's FLAC's fault
